e this place. You could push through the trees in any direction, and paths lead west and east.                                                  You are plunging through dense undergrowth in a thick forest, deftly avoiding thorns and briars. The forest continues to the north and northeast, but thins out in all other directions.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        You are fighting your way through extremely dense forest, avoiding vicious undergrowth and thorns which catch your legs and try to trip you. The forest is so dense here that it completely obscures your view in almost every direction; but to the north you can see what looks like a huge wall of stone - perhaps a cliff - which blocks your way in that direction, while to the west you notice the trees grow less dense and you can enter a clearing.                                                                   You are in a bright, open area of the forest, where the trees are widely spread. The forest continues in all directions except west, where the trees give way abruptly to grassland; to the northeast you notice a patch of tall, melancholy conifers among the deciduous trees of the wood.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    You are in a very dark, gloomy area of the woods. Solemn dark trees stand in silence all around you and a feeling of melancholy pervades the air. To the north you can see the base of a massive towering cliff, and to the south is a path overhung by trees.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  You have entered a part of the forest where the trees are very thorny. They rip at you as you push through them, tearing your clothes and skin. The thorns get even denser to the north, making it impossible to continue in that direction, but in other directions they give way to normal trees. To the south you can see a path.                                                                                                                                                                                            You are standing in a grove of very ancient trees. There is hardly any light, and no sound, and you feel an indefinable aura of menace from the trees around you. Southwards you can see a path, and southeast is a clearing; west the woods continue, but to the north a high cliff blocks your way, and further to the east through the trees you can see some kind of stone building.                                                                                                                                        You are walking through pleasant pasture lands close to the south side of a tall mountain which dominates the nearby land. Westwards you can see a well - paved road beside a deep wide river, leading towards a bright city far to the southwest; eastwards a green hill rises from the marshlands further southeast, crowned with some sort of ruined building, and south the pasture lands continue.                                                                                                                         You are fighting your way desperately through evil trees which clutch at you with gnarled branches and try to trip you with roots. The forest is so thick here that you cannot see any end to the trees, except to the east where there is some sort of building visible through the forest.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    You are in a very dark part of the forest. The trees here block almost all of the light, letting only a sort of dim glow filter through their tangled branches. To the north is a path; in other directions the forest continues, thinning out somewhat to the west and south.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  You are walking along a grassy path which leads east and west. To north and south the path is surrounded by wide stretches of grass; the path joins another, wider path to the west, in which direction you can see the sea. Northeast is the edge of a forest, and southeast rises a steep hill, while some distance further east you can make out the flat peak of a high mountain.                                                                                                                                           You are in a dim part of the woods, shaded by the tall dark trees all around you. Through the trees to the east you can see a glint of water.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   This is a narrow east-west path through the forest, dark and shadowy because of the great trees overhanging it on either side. To the east is a small clearing, while to the west the darkness is somewhat less; or you could plunge into the threatening woods on either side of the path.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     You are in a part of the forest entirely composed of oak trees. They are all magnificent specimens, and some of them must be many centuries old. To the north you can see a forest path; to the west the oaks give way to birches, while to the east the trees are thicker and more tangled.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    This is the northeastern end of a wide stone road which runs along the eastern side of a broad and fast northeast/southwest river. Northeast are the lower slopes of a mountain, from which the river flows; you can cross the river via a sturdy and new-looking wooden bridge, to the west, or you can wander off into pasture land to the south, southeast and east.                                                                                                                                                         You are in a small grove of graceful silver birch trees. Birds sing in the branches and the atmosphere is calm and pleasant. Through the trees to the east you can see the sturdier forms of oaks merging with the birches, and to the west is a junction of forest paths. You can also join a path to the north, but in other directions the forest continues.                                                                                                                                                                 This is a broad stone-flagged east-west road which leads towards a city in the west. The road itself stops here, at the foot of a steep and possibly man-made hill to the east; 