can see the sea.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                This is an area of sticky mud and flourishing green plants on the edges of deeper swamp to the south, west and east. The land around is very flat, (perhaps contributing to the marshiness) but some distance off to the northwest and northeast you can see low hills which must be drier, while further still northwesterly is a high mountain. To the south is the sea.                                                                                                                                                      You're on wet, squelchy land, to the southeast of a low hill and close to the centre of a foul marsh to the southwest. Black water oozes round your feet as you stand here, and the mud gapes at your feet with a soft sucking sound, while a chill and evil-smelling wind blows off the sea and the mudflats further south. This is a desolate place. Further north is drier land, a valley between low grassy hills.                                                                                                          You are on bleak mudflats north of the sea. To the north are dreary wetlands. West and east the brown foul-smelling mud continues.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              You are floundering in sticky brown mudflats north of the sea. The mud clings to your feet and seems to be sucking you down.... You can leave, quickly, by continuing west along the coast of the realm (where the mud continues) or by going in any other direction, where the mud gives way to marshes and swamp.                                                                                                                                                                                                             You are in a grey swamp area north of the sea. West and east are sticky mudflats, and in all other directions are flat wetlands.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                You are on a high green hilltop overlooking the land. To the east and west are swift rivers, and northwards, a mountain. Far to the west is a marsh, and south are grasslands, wetlands, mudflats, and finally the sea. About you are the ruins of a watchtower; once a stronghold and vantage point, this is now ruined and blackened by fire, and in places little of it remains save the foundations. The hilltop continues south.                                                                                           You are in a grey featureless swamp. North and east this bleak fen country stretches on, its monotony broken to the northeast by a tall white building of some kind. South is a grey and listless sea; west are bleak mudflats. Gloom pervades this place.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      This is the centre of a wide grassy plain stretching off to the north and south. Southwest and southeast are two low grassy hills which you can ascend; some way