ldlands.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        You are in coldlands southwest of black cliffs and southeast of Hamlet's castle. This location has no features of interest whatsoever.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          You are at the gateway to Hamlet's castle, a great wood - and - iron affair, with Hamlet's monogram painted on in black. About you stretch barren coldlands, south to a chasm from which a great steam rises.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   You are between cliffs to your north and south, in a fairly broad open passage to a structure of ice at the eastern end. There is a way out southwest from here between the south cliff and a sheer steep ice hill to the west.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 You are clinging frantically to the meagre handholds to be found in the sheer black walls of a circular pit. Although evidently hand and footholds were once cut in the rock, they have been worn almost completely away - presumably by frequent use. This is not a place to stop and admire the view, as you will soon lose your grip; you could, however, haul yourself up over the edge of the pit and to safety, or descend into the depths below.                                                                         You are walking along a wide man-made rock tunnel which slopes downward to the south and upward to the north, whence you can detect a glimmer of light. Southward the darkness is absolute and nothing can be seen. A whisper of cold air blows up the tunnel.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  You are standing in a vast subterranean hall deep beneath the mountainside. Its black walls, smooth and polished as glass, soar upwards to a vaulted and arched roof many hundreds of feet above. Every sound you make is magnified and reverberates about the cavern, making you feel extremely exposed despite the millions of tons of rock all around you. Illuminated by your flickering light you can see an upward-sloping tunnel to the north and three sinister black archways to west, east and south.                 You are in a small alcove below a flight of spiral stairs which lead up into darkness. To the west a tall archway, hewn from black stone as are the steps and the very walls of the chamber, leads into a vast space of impenetrable blackness.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 You are in a short east - west passage with a low roof, hewn from glittering black rock. To the east the passage passes though a high archway into a wide chamber of some kind, while to the west a low flight of steps leads deeper underground.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               You have entered a large room almost completely filled with life - size stone statues of every kind. They seem to be made of the same black, glittering stone as the walls, ceiling and floor, and are incredibly lifelike in their execution. All seem to have been captured in the middle of some action, as if frozen in the stone. Archways of the same black stone are to the south and north of this chamber.                                                                                                             You are on a flight of spiral steps which lead both up and down from here. The treads of the stairs are slippery, being made from stone worn smooth by countless feet. All around is darkness and silence.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      You are now in a narrow hallway whose walls, ceiling and floor are made from stone so brightly polished as to act as a mirror. Myriad reflections dance around you, distorted and weird, and make you dizzy and confused. You are no longer sure where you came in, or how to get out....                                                                                                                                                                                                                       